cs.NA, cs.DC, cs.AR, cs.DS, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The paper discusses the optimization of numerical algorithms for multi-core processors, specifically focusing on sparse matrix-vector multiplications. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper investigates the performance of sparse MVM implementations on state-of-the-art multi-core systems, which falls under the domain of parallel computing. 
- cs.AR (Hardware Architecture): The paper discusses the impact of hardware architecture (multi-core processors) on the performance of numerical algorithms. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses two different storage schemes and computational kernels for sparse MVM, which falls under the domain of data structures and algorithms. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses the optimization of existing algorithms, which falls under the domain of software engineering.
